ArrayList:
----------
ArrayList can grow or shrink dynamically as elements are added or removed. 
It is found in the java.util package.

Key Features:
Dynamic Sizing: Automatically resizes when elements are added or removed.
Index-Based Access: Allows random access to elements using an index, similar to arrays.
Duplicates: Allows duplicate elements.
Ordered Collection: Maintains the insertion order.
Nulls Allowed: Can store null elements.

Common Methods:
add(element): Adds an element to the end of the list.
add(index, element): Inserts an element at the specified index.
get(index): Retrieves the element at the specified index.
set(index, element): Updates the element at the specified index.
remove(index): Removes the element at the specified index.
remove(object): Removes the first occurrence of the specified object.
size(): Returns the number of elements in the list.
contains(object): Checks if the list contains the specified object.
clear(): Removes all elements from the list.
isEmpty(): Checks if the list is empty.